This reporter learned from the Beijing Gardening and Greening Bureau that in celebration of the 70th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China, Beijing plans to fully improve the landscape along Chang’an Street and its axis and thereby create a harmonious and happy atmosphere.
At present, 12 three-dimensional flower beds have been totally completed and debuted, ensuring that now, more than 20 million pots of flowers decorate the capital city in celebration of National Day.
